=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: 2-Chloronicotinic acid → 2-chloronicotinamide by SOCl2 (cat. DMF) to the acid chloride, then NH3/MeOH or NH4OH to form the primary amide. | Step 2: 2-Chloronicotinamide → 2-aminonicotinamide by ammonolysis of the 2-chloro group (NH3 in EtOH, heat/sealed tube). | Step 3: 2-Aminonicotinamide + N-Boc-4-piperidone → N-Boc-protected spiro[piperidine-4,2'-pyrido-fused dihydroquinazolin-4'-one] via acid-promoted cyclocondensation (e.g., AcOH or p-TsOH, heat): imine formation with the ketone followed by ring closure to the spiro lactam. | Step 4: Boc deprotection of that spiro intermediate with TFA/CH2Cl2 or HCl/dioxane → O=C1Nc2cnccc2C12CCNCC2 (free piperidine NH target).

